		<li id="comment-1255">
		
		<div class="commentcont">
							
			<p>To those having issues with hover colors, it doesn\&#8217;t work as expected because of the way the colors get applied to the links (via inline styles in the <a> tag itself).  It can be made to work, however.  All you need to do is add the CSS \&#8221;!important\&#8221; declaration to the color property for the hover style&#8230;do something like this, and it will work for you: </p>
<p>.ctc a:hover {<br />
	color: #f00 !important;<br />
} </p>
<p>The \&#8221;!important\&#8221; tells the css engine to override all styles with this one.</a></p>
				
				<p>
									</p>
		
		</div>
		
		<cite>
		
		Posted by <span class="commentauthor"><a href='http://reciprocity.be/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Keith</a></span> | <a href="#comment-1255" title="">May 21, 2009, 12:16 pm</a> 						
		
		</cite>
		
		
		</li>
		
	
	
